  "body": "Following on work done for fixing the async pending transactions [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/3839), the following follow-up tasks are nice to have optimizations\r\n- Use the `EventPendingTransactionStatusChanged` notifications along with `Delete` to watch and confirm (if autodelete is not required)\r\n- Trigger transaction download on pending status change, not to wait for the next scan\r\n- Replace `eth_getTransactionByHash` with `eth_getTransactionReceipt` to detect if the transaction is still pending and extract and store the status\r\n- Now, if both sender and receiver are in the wallet list, the first downloaded transaction will convert the pending entry. Optimize to do it for the one that the sender is in.",
